## The current behavior

When deleting an item, the UI is not refreshed.

## The expected behavior

With revalidatePath, we should have an UI up to date after deleting an element.

The react-hooks/set-state-in-effect rule fails to flag a violation when a component's destructured prop has a default value that is a NewExpression (new Foo()).

react version: 18.3.1
eslint-plugin-react-hooks: 7.0.1

## Steps To Reproduce

```tsx
// ❌ Should flag — but doesn't
function MyComponent({ value = new Number() }) {
  const [x, setX] = useState(false)

  useEffect(() => {
    setX(true)
  }, [x])

  return null
}

// ✅ Correctly flags — literal default
function MyComponent({ value = Number() }) {
  const [x, setX] = useState(false)

  useEffect(() => {
    setX(true)
  }, [x])

  return null
}
```

Since React 19 devs can pass `ref` directly as a prop (forwardref is not needed anymore) , but now `eslint-plugin-react-hooks` is complaining about valid code 


